  "title": "Quality Assurance Technician (Automotive)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Basic up to $3000</li><li>5.25 days | 8.30am-6pm </li><li>Location: Ubi </li></ul><p>Job scope: </p><ul><li>Check and confirm that all vehicle servicing and repair work is properly completed before handover, ensuring it meets Audi standards and customer expectations.</li><li>Diagnose and troubleshoot vehicle issues, especially complex or repeated problems, and work closely with the Foreman and Workshop Supervisor to verify that repairs are done correctly</li><li>Support daily workshop operations by providing technical advice to technicians and assisting with test drives and service-related matters together with service advisors.</li><li>Identify any additional or outstanding repair works and report them promptly to the Foreman, giving clear recommendations to maintain repair quality and prevent customer complaints.</li></ul><p>Requirements: </p><p><p><ul><li>Minimum 3 years' experience as a QC Accessor or similar role in an automotive repair workshop</li><li>Valid Class 3 driving license</li></ul><p><br />For consideration, kindly submit your CV by clicking “APPLY NOW”<br /></p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates would be notified</em>*<br /></p><p>MTC Consulting Pte Ltd | 15C7752</p><p>R24124448 | Nana Yeoh Li Xuan</p></p></p>",
